                <note rend="inline" type="source">458.11 Dexter and Carpenter/194: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Sweden (<persName type="from"
                            >Steinhardt</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stockholm</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-09-30T13:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 30, 1933—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 30—9:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>26. I have just received a check of the Swedish Riksbank drawn on National City
                    Bank of New York City for $150,000 payable to Haight, Smith, Griffen and Deming,
                    attorneys for Dexter and Carpenter, Incorporated.</p>
                <p>I am sending check to the Department by registered mail today via the steamship
                        <hi rend="italic">Ile de France</hi> due New York October 10th.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
